Medidas vs distribuciones

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from ggplot import mtcars

## C:\Users\ruben\AppData\Local\R-MINI~1\envs\R-RETI~1\lib\site-packages\ggplot\utils.py:81: FutureWarning: pandas.tslib is deprecated and will be removed in a future version.
## You can access Timestamp as pandas.Timestamp
##   pd.tslib.Timestamp,
## C:\Users\ruben\OneDrive\Documentos\R\win-library\4.1\reticulate\python\rpytools\loader.py:44: FutureWarning: The pandas.lib module is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. These are private functions and can be accessed from pandas._libs.lib instead
##   level=level
norm_data = pd.DataFrame(np.random.normal(size=100000))

norm_data.plot(kind = "density", figsize=(10,10))
## <AxesSubplot:ylabel='Density'>
plt.vlines(norm_data.mean(), ymin=0, ymax=0.4, linewidth=5, color="green")
## <matplotlib.collections.LineCollection object at 0x0000000026C8B2E8>
plt.vlines(norm_data.median(), ymin=0, ymax=0.4, linewidth=2.0, color="red")
## <matplotlib.collections.LineCollection object at 0x00000000315C7518>
plt.show()


plt.clf()
skewed_data = pd.DataFrame(np.random.exponential(size=100000))

skewed_data.plot(kind = "density", figsize=(10,10), xlim=(-5,5))
## <AxesSubplot:ylabel='Density'>
plt.vlines(skewed_data.mean(), ymin=0, ymax=1, linewidth=5, color="green")
## <matplotlib.collections.LineCollection object at 0x000000003157A4A8>
plt.vlines(skewed_data.median(), ymin=0, ymax=1, linewidth=2.0, color="red")
## <matplotlib.collections.LineCollection object at 0x00000000316A7EF0>
plt.show()


norm_data = np.random.normal(size=50)
outliers = np.random.normal(15, size=3)

combined_data = pd.DataFrame(np.concatenate((norm_data, outliers), axis=0))






combined_data.plot(kind = "density", figsize=(10,10), xlim=(-5,20))

## <AxesSubplot:ylabel='Density'>
plt.vlines(combined_data.mean(), ymin=0, ymax=0.2, linewidth=5, color="green")
## <matplotlib.collections.LineCollection object at 0x0000000031C8C748>
plt.vlines(combined_data.median(), ymin=0, ymax=0.2, linewidth=2.0, color="red")
